      ipInterceptor is a TCP/UDP trace utility designed
      for developers, QA teams, support staff, and       
      admin. Unlike other TCP trace utilities, it 
      captures and re-assembles packets into related
      SEND/RECIEVE conversations, which is how a 
      developer would want to see it. 
                                                                        
      ipIntercetpor is especially useful for Web 
      developers, or anyone that wants to capture and
      analyze TCP/UDP traffic on a local workstation
      or server. It produces log files that show either
      raw data, or CSV formatted output with very
      granular response time numbers for each 
      conversation. It graphs IP traffic and shows data
      in either TEXT or HEX format.

      Users can filter IP or port. Web developers can 
      view HTTP Headers, XML, POST commands, cookies,     
      CSS, Java Script.

      Version 2.1.9 may include unspecified updates,
